KEY POINT (informal summary, not legal text):

If you modify this code and run it as a network service (i.e. host a
website using a derivative of this code), AGPL-3.0 requires that you
make the complete corresponding source of your derivative available
to every user of that service, under this same license.

In short: forks must stay open. Private modifications used internally
are fine; public-facing modified deployments must publish their source.

